seaman’s name for albatross. So that by no possibility could Coleridge’s 
wild Rhyme have had aught to do with those mystical impressions which were 
mine, when I saw that bird upon our deck. For neither had I then read the 
Rhyme, nor knew the bird to be an albatross. Yet, in saying this, I do but 
